name: Rose Gardner
bio: Hi everyone! My name is Rose Gardner (I know haha) and I pledged at Psi U during the Fall of 2017, my first semester at Georgia Tech. I really enjoy chemistry, which is a must if you're going to be majoring in it tbh. But besides drowning in class work, I enjoy being around all my brothers at the fraternity, specifically if we're playing video games or just generally goofing off. Recently we've all been playing Terraria or GTA V together, but I'm also a big fan of single player RPGs and open world games. Skyrim, Fallout, Final Fantasy XV, and Kingdom Hearts are just a few of the games I really love. I'm also one of the few people at Psi U that really likes K-pop, I am always down to talk about your groups if you want!! Oh also talk to me if you watch One Piece, you know who you are.
psiUBrags: Worked in a chemistry lab Spring 2020 doing research on inorganic and metallic metal membranes. Working as a TA in Synth Lab 1 during Fall 2020.

name: Randall Kliman
bio: I am a 4th year Computer Engineering Major with a Minor in Robotics. I was born in Tucson, Arizona and spent 12 years of my life there before moving to Washington, D.C. in 2011. I've always been interested in technology and robotics while also holding a passion for art. In my free time I play video games, play Dungeons and Dragons, watch Star Trek, and on some days I can be found giving unsolicited "wisdom" in our foyer. I joined Psi Upsilon in 2018 and it's been one of the best decisions I've ever made. Other organizations that i'm involved with on campus include Georgia Tech's IEEE chapter and GT's own WREK Radio.
psiUBrags: I've had the opportunity to work in a couple of robotics research labs over the past few years and I am currently working in Georgia Tech's Agile Locomotion Lab on quadruped robots.
